.TH SESHAT 1 "" "seshat @VERSION@" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
seshat \- data and software repository system
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B seshat
.I subcommand
.RI [ options ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B seshat
is a data and software repository system.
It provides a web interface for managing and publishing research data and software.
.SH SUBCOMMANDS
.SS web
Start the seshat web server.
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Show a help message.
.TP
.BR \-c ", " \-\-config\-file =\fIFILE\fR
Load configuration from
.IR FILE .
.TP
.BR \-i ", " \-\-initialize
Populate the RDF store with default triples.
.TP
.BR \-e ", " \-\-extract\-transactions\-from\-log =\fIDATETIME\fR
Extract transactions from the log file. Does not extract delayed transactions.
The optional argument is a datetime to start from, in the format
.IR "YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM:SS" .
.TP
.BR \-d ", " \-\-extract\-delayed\-transactions\-from\-log =\fIDATETIME\fR
Similar to
.BR \-e ,
except this option only extracts delayed transactions from the log file.
.TP
.BR \-A ", " \-\-apply\-transactions =\fIDIR\fR
Apply transactions extracted by the
.B \-e
option. The optional argument is the path to the folder containing the SPARQL
transaction files. By default it will look in the pre-configured directory.
.TP
.BR \-f ", " \-\-full\-rdf\-export
Export all metadata as RDF triples in N3 format.
.RB "Note: This feature is in " BETA " state."
.TP
.BR \-p ", " \-\-public\-rdf\-export
Export all publicly available metadata as RDF triples in N3 format.
.RB "Note: This feature is in " BETA " state."
.SH "GLOBAL OPTIONS"
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Show a help message.
.TP
.BR \-v ", " \-\-version
Show versioning information.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /etc/seshat/seshat-example-config.xml
Example configuration file.
.SH "SEE ALSO"
The full documentation for
.B seshat
is available in
.IR /usr/share/seshat/index.html .
